               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-752" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-752" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-752" type="surname" value="HARDING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-752" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HARDING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to William Dedman, a grocer in Bryanstone-street—I missed a pair of scales and weight off the counter on the 28th of May—these are them—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-753" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-753" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-753" type="surname" value="STARR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-753" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN STARR</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at the prosecutor's. On the afternoon of the 28th of May, between four and five o'clock, I was sitting in the parlour adjoin<lb></lb>ing the shop—the prisoner came in with some mats, to know if we wanted any—she was told there were none wanted—she went out and came again in about ten minutes, and I heard a noise—I saw her go out—I followed her, and took the scales from her, with the assistance of a young man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
